# Vite Configuration

Vite configuration lives in `vite.config.ts` (or `.js`/`.mts`/`.mjs`) at the project root. The `defineConfig` helper from `vite` provides full type safety without manual type annotations.

## Basic Config

```typescript
// vite.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react';

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  resolve: {
    alias: {
      '@': '/src',
    },
  },
});
```

The config file is auto-detected in this order: `vite.config.ts`, `vite.config.mts`, `vite.config.js`, `vite.config.mjs`, `vite.config.cjs`, `vite.config.cts`. Use `--config path/to/config.ts` to specify a custom location.

## Conditional Config

Pass a function to `defineConfig` to access the current command and mode:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';

export default defineConfig(({ command, mode, isSsrBuild, isPreview }) => {
  if (command === 'serve') {
    // Dev-specific config
    return {
      define: {
        __DEV__: true,
      },
    };
  } else {
    // Build-specific config (command === 'build')
    return {
      define: {
        __DEV__: false,
      },
    };
  }
});
```

`command` is `'serve'` during dev (`vite`, `vite dev`, `vite serve`) and `'build'` during production (`vite build`). `mode` defaults to `'development'` for serve and `'production'` for build, but can be overridden with `--mode`.

## Async Config

The config function can be async â€” useful for dynamic imports or fetching configuration:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';

export default defineConfig(async ({ command, mode }) => {
  const data = await fetchRemoteConfig();
  return {
    define: {
      __API_URL__: JSON.stringify(data.apiUrl),
    },
  };
});
```

## Using loadEnv

`import.meta.env` is not available inside the config file. Use `loadEnv` to read `.env` values during configuration:

```typescript
import { defineConfig, loadEnv } from 'vite';

export default defineConfig(({ mode }) => {
  // Load all env vars (including those without VITE_ prefix)
  const env = loadEnv(mode, process.cwd(), '');

  return {
    define: {
      __APP_TITLE__: JSON.stringify(env.APP_TITLE),
    },
    server: {
      proxy: {
        '/api': {
          target: env.API_URL,
          changeOrigin: true,
        },
      },
    },
  };
});
```

The third argument to `loadEnv` controls which prefixes to load. Pass `''` (empty string) to load all env vars, not just `VITE_`-prefixed ones. Pass `['VITE_', 'APP_']` to load multiple prefixes. See [[vite/env]] for full `.env` file behavior.

## resolve.alias

Set up path aliases so `import Foo from '@/components/Foo'` resolves to `./src/components/Foo`:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import path from 'node:path';

export default defineConfig({
  resolve: {
    alias: {
      '@': path.resolve(__dirname, 'src'),
      '@components': path.resolve(__dirname, 'src/components'),
      '@utils': path.resolve(__dirname, 'src/utils'),
      '@assets': path.resolve(__dirname, 'src/assets'),
    },
  },
});
```

For TypeScript projects, mirror these aliases in `tsconfig.json` so the compiler resolves them too. See [[typescript/config]] for `paths` configuration:

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["src/*"],
      "@components/*": ["src/components/*"],
      "@utils/*": ["src/utils/*"],
      "@assets/*": ["src/assets/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

Alternatively, use the `vite-tsconfig-paths` plugin to automatically read aliases from tsconfig.json, avoiding duplication.

## CSS Configuration

Vite handles CSS out of the box. Configure modules, preprocessors, and PostCSS via the `css` option:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';

export default defineConfig({
  css: {
    // CSS Modules options
    modules: {
      localsConvention: 'camelCaseOnly',  // export class names as camelCase
      scopeBehaviour: 'local',            // default: 'local'
      generateScopedName: '[name]__[local]___[hash:base64:5]',
    },

    // Preprocessor options (requires installing the preprocessor)
    preprocessorOptions: {
      scss: {
        // Inject variables/mixins into every .scss file
        additionalData: `@use "@/styles/variables" as *;`,
        api: 'modern-compiler',  // use modern Sass API (recommended)
      },
      less: {
        math: 'always',
        globalVars: {
          primaryColor: '#4f46e5',
        },
      },
    },

    // PostCSS config (overrides postcss.config.js)
    postcss: {
      plugins: [
        // inline PostCSS plugins
      ],
    },

    // Use Lightning CSS instead of PostCSS (experimental)
    // lightningcss: {
    //   targets: browserslistToTargets(browserslist('>= 0.25%')),
    // },
  },
});
```

CSS Modules are activated by naming files with `.module.css` (or `.module.scss`, `.module.less`). Install preprocessors separately: `npm i -D sass` for Sass, `npm i -D less` for Less, `npm i -D stylus` for Stylus.

## define â€” Global Constants

Replace global identifiers at build time. Values are replaced as-is during development and statically replaced during build:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';

export default defineConfig({
  define: {
    __APP_VERSION__: JSON.stringify('1.2.3'),
    __BUILD_TIME__: JSON.stringify(new Date().toISOString()),
    __DEV__: JSON.stringify(process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production'),
    'process.env.CUSTOM': JSON.stringify('value'),
  },
});
```

String values must be wrapped in `JSON.stringify()` so they include quotes in the replacement. For TypeScript, declare the globals in a `.d.ts` file:

```typescript
// src/env.d.ts
declare const __APP_VERSION__: string;
declare const __BUILD_TIME__: string;
declare const __DEV__: boolean;
```

## Framework Plugin Quick Reference

| Framework | Plugin Package | Import |
|-----------|---------------|--------|
| React | `@vitejs/plugin-react` | `import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'` |
| React (SWC) | `@vitejs/plugin-react-swc` | `import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react-swc'` |
| Vue | `@vitejs/plugin-vue` | `import vue from '@vitejs/plugin-vue'` |
| Svelte | `@sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte` | `import { svelte } from '@sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte'` |
| Solid | `vite-plugin-solid` | `import solid from 'vite-plugin-solid'` |
| Preact | `@preact/preset-vite` | `import preact from '@preact/preset-vite'` |

See [[vite/plugins]] for plugin authoring and advanced plugin configuration.

## All Shared Options

| Option | Type | Default | Description |
|--------|------|---------|-------------|
| `root` | `string` | `process.cwd()` | Project root directory |
| `base` | `string` | `'/'` | Public base path for deployment |
| `mode` | `string` | `'development'`/`'production'` | Environment mode |
| `define` | `Record<string, any>` | â€” | Global constant replacements |
| `plugins` | `(Plugin \| Plugin[])[]` | `[]` | Vite/Rollup plugins |
| `publicDir` | `string \| false` | `'public'` | Static asset directory |
| `cacheDir` | `string` | `'node_modules/.vite'` | Pre-bundle cache directory |
| `resolve.alias` | `Record<string, string>` | â€” | Import path aliases |
| `resolve.extensions` | `string[]` | `['.mjs', '.js', '.mts', '.ts', '.jsx', '.tsx', '.json']` | Import resolution extensions |
| `envDir` | `string` | `root` | Directory to search for .env files |
| `envPrefix` | `string \| string[]` | `'VITE_'` | Env vars exposed to client |
| `appType` | `'spa' \| 'mpa' \| 'custom'` | `'spa'` | Application type |
| `logLevel` | `'info' \| 'warn' \| 'error' \| 'silent'` | `'info'` | Console output level |
| `assetsInclude` | `string \| RegExp \| (string \| RegExp)[]` | â€” | Extra asset file patterns |
